1. we category container to 3 type, service container, data container(volume), log container(volume), config container(volume)

2, for server image, according to service, may create some data volume on it. because data volume will copy init content from image, use this volume to customize config. for example, a nginx service image, we can create a /etc/nginx data volume.

3, every image has a /m3958baseconfig directory, in which has,dnsmasq.conf,supervisord.conf, and addn_host file. use:
 docker run -d -v /m3958baseconfig --name servicename-base-config-vol  m3958/base:201401 echo base config
to create a named vol to customize content.

4. every service container use supervisord to start, default has dnsmasq started, you can read supervisord.conf.
5. container name conventions. 

service container: appname-servicename-service, for example: piwik-nginx-service
data container: appname-dataname-usageservicename..-data-vol
log container: appname-servicename-log-vol
base config container: appname-servicename-baseconfig-vol
config container: appname-servicename-config-vol
